{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place plain flour, 1 Tbsp oil, 1 pinch salt and 1 pinch black pepper in mixing bowl then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Place a jug on mixing bowl lid and weigh in water. Without measuring cup, set <b>speed 3<b> and gradually add water until dough comes together. Knead <b>3 min\/<b>. Transfer to an oiled bowl and cover with a tea towel. Leave to rest for 1 hour. Meanwhile, prepare filling.","Place onion, garlic and parsley in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add chard, remaining 1 Tbsp oil, 1 pinch salt and 1 pinch pepper then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Preheat oven to 190°C and line a large baking tray (approx. 40 cm x 30 cm) with baking paper.","When dough has rested, divide into two pieces. Roll one piece out as thinly as possible to fit prepared baking tray (approx. 40 cm x 30 cm). Place on baking tray. Spread filling over right up to edges of pastry.","Roll out second piece of dough to same size then place over filling. Use a rolling pin to lightly press layers together (removing air) and seal edges tightly. Make a few small holes in the top with a fork. Bake for 20 minutes (190°C) until lightly browned.","Cut in diamonds using a knife or pizza cutter and serve warm drizzled with extra virgin olive oil."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["300 g plain flour","2 Tbsp olive oil, plus extra for greasing","2 pinches fine sea salt","2 pinches ground black pepper","150 g water","100 g onions, quartered","3 garlic cloves","4 Tbsp fresh parsley, leaves only","100 g rainbow chard, stems removed, leaves sliced","extra virgin olive oil, for drizzling"]}],"id":"r314685","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-MxHOzK31I5w\/XZaoXbXpWZI\/AAAAAAAAhJY\/cR9O9DW4nWUV7Zb6U2Q70dIez5-RoUjOACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lKRSADtWxmXxAnQg.png","title":"Soparnik","publishedAt":"2018-04-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"34 g","fat":"40 g","uom":"per 22 pieces","carbohydrates":"234 g","calories":"6230 kJ \/ 1479 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rolling pin, tea towel, jug, large baking tray, baking paper, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Soparnik is a traditional Dalmatian dish. It was first considered for fasting or food for the poor, being made from a simple dough of plain flour, water, salt and a splash of olive oil then filled with chard. It is now declared as part of the cultural heritage of Croatia."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 45m","22 pieces"]}